# Covenant v2 Project Configuration

## Python Environment
- Use Python interpreter: .venv/bin/python
- Virtual environment is located at: .venv/
- Jupyter kernel: covenantv2

## Project Structure
- Main configuration: config_local.yaml
- Model outputs: model_outputs/
- Notebooks: notebooks/
- Data: ../covenant/SampleCovenantData/

## Key Files
- main.py: Main entry point
- modelv1/updated_failure.py: Scott model implementation
- modelv2/: New model implementations
- requirements.txt: Python dependencies

## Development Workflow
- Use 'make jupyter' to start Jupyter with correct environment
- Use 'make test-run MODEL=<type>' for testing models
- Use 'make run-prod MODEL=<type>' for production runs
- Always select 'Covenant v2 Environment' kernel in Jupyter notebooks

## Environment Setup
- Virtual environment: .venv/
- Python version: 3.13
- Key packages: pandas, numpy, scikit-learn, lightgbm, optuna, yfinance 